1
00:00:10,636 --> 00:00:13,388
[SHIROU] I remember it first
happening when I was a kid.

2
00:00:13,472 --> 00:00:15,807
Maybe ten years ago?

3
00:00:15,891 --> 00:00:18,936
There was some trouble going
on way too close to home.

4
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:22,272
So I decided to solve it
the fastest way I knew how.

5
00:00:22,356 --> 00:00:24,983
The whole time I felt
weird and disconnected.

6
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:26,568
I thought,

7
00:00:26,652 --> 00:00:31,198
"This is familiar, I feel like
I've already done this before."

8
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:32,950
It was déjà vu.

9
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,285
That's where you do something
for the very first time,

10
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:37,913
but it somehow seems
like it's your hundredth.

11
00:00:37,996 --> 00:00:41,500
No matter what I try, I haven't
been able to shake that feeling.

12
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:43,335
Calling it shitty
doesn't even come close

13
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:45,963
to describing how
frustrating it is.

14
00:00:46,046 --> 00:00:48,048
I can't use it to plan
for things ahead of time,

15
00:00:48,131 --> 00:00:50,133
'cause it won't let me
see into the future.

16
00:00:50,217 --> 00:00:52,761
Instead, everything just
seems played out.

17
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:55,222
It's boring. I want a surprise!

18
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:57,224
That's why I live
life on the edge.

19
00:00:57,307 --> 00:00:59,518
Hang out with society's rejects.

20
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:03,146
And do whatever I can
to kill this déjà vu.

21
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:06,024
I'm not afraid of dying
if that means it'll stop.

22
00:01:06,108 --> 00:01:07,526
Hell, it'll be worth it.

23
00:01:07,609 --> 00:01:10,737
First time I'd feel
alive in a decade.

24
00:01:10,821 --> 00:01:12,072
But here's the kick,

25
00:01:12,155 --> 00:01:14,866
and this is where it
starts to get really weird.

26
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:16,952
Whenever I feel this déjà vu,

27
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:21,164
for whatever reason, no matter
what I do, I just can't die.

28
00:01:21,248 --> 00:01:24,167
A passing stallion
enters into the fray.

29
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,254
[SHIROU]
Hilarious, huh?

30
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:30,632
Like a third‐rate pulp
hero who just can't lose.

31
00:01:30,716 --> 00:01:33,594
One of God's
miserable playthings.

32
00:01:34,386 --> 00:01:39,349
♪

33
00:03:06,645 --> 00:03:11,108
Shirou...! What the
hell's wrong with you?

34
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:13,610
I thought I told you to
stay out of my business!

35
00:03:13,694 --> 00:03:16,446
[SHIROU] Shut up.
Hate to break it to ya,

36
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:19,032
but my life doesn't
revolve around you, chief.

37
00:03:19,116 --> 00:03:21,702
I'm the star of my
own story, understand?

38
00:03:21,785 --> 00:03:24,871
So maybe you should stay
the hell outta my way!

39
00:03:24,955 --> 00:03:25,914
[WILHELM grunts]

40
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:28,750
[WILHELM]
What are you doing?

41
00:03:28,834 --> 00:03:31,336
Who do you think you are,
barging in like this?

42
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:32,754
[SHIROU]
Hm.

43
00:03:32,838 --> 00:03:34,381
Looks like I'll need to teach
you not to pop up out

44
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:37,634
of nowhere, babbling nonsense
while I'm working!

45
00:03:37,718 --> 00:03:39,052
[WILHELM shouts]

46
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:44,933
Déjà vu. You've done all
of this before, Milky.

47
00:03:46,143 --> 00:03:49,771
[SHIROU] And it's the same damn
thing with me. Come on, now.

48
00:03:49,855 --> 00:03:52,190
You can do better
than that, can't ya?

49
00:03:52,274 --> 00:03:54,943
Or else I'll never
shake this feeling.

50
00:03:55,026 --> 00:03:57,654
This new one. Who's he?

51
00:04:00,949 --> 00:04:05,704
Know what? I've changed
my mind. You can have the kid.

52
00:04:07,122 --> 00:04:08,206
I understand.

53
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:09,583
Looks like our new playmates

54
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:13,503
have settled on a plan
of attack. No, backing out.

55
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:15,922
Don't gimme that look,
you saw what happened.

56
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:19,217
It's pretty obvious I can hold
my own with these creeps.

57
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:22,637
Seems like it, but remember
what I told you.

58
00:04:22,721 --> 00:04:25,640
I refuse to help
you commit suicide.

59
00:04:25,724 --> 00:04:28,727
So don't die on me,
you dumbass!

60
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:29,978
[chuckels]

61
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,149
[grunts]

62
00:04:43,575 --> 00:04:44,493
[SHIROU chuckles]

63
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:46,536
You're quick for
an ordinary human.

64
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:51,666
The way that you move, you're
used to this. But is that all?

65
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:54,377
[WILHELM grunts]

66
00:05:00,342 --> 00:05:05,305
[SHIROU, WILHELM grunting]

67
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:10,060
[WILHELM]
Oh! You dodged that one.

68
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:13,188
I was even putting a little
effort into it that time.

69
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:17,859
So be it. Looks like you pass
the test, though just barely.

70
00:05:17,943 --> 00:05:20,737
Why don't you tell
me what your name is?

71
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:24,199
[SHIROU] I'm Shirou Yusa.
Though that won't matter.

72
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:25,534
Least not to you.

73
00:05:25,617 --> 00:05:27,494
Cause you're gonna be dead
here in just a minute.

74
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:28,036
[bones snapping]

75
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:33,041
[WILHELM laughs]

76
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:40,382
[WILHELM] Tough news, boy.
I can't die at night.

77
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:42,509
They would never
let that happen.

78
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:44,970
They want to keep me alive.

79
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,975
So be proud, you little punk.

80
00:05:50,058 --> 00:05:53,228
It's been almost 40 years since
I used this technique in a fight

81
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:56,189
with a regular human,
and when I get like this,

82
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:58,149
I can't hold back.

83
00:05:58,233 --> 00:06:00,485
They all start
screaming at me.

84
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:03,113
Telling me they
thirst for blood!

85
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:04,573
[SHIROU grunts]

86
00:06:10,245 --> 00:06:11,413
[grunts]

87
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:17,419
[WILHELM]
Does that hurt? I bet it does.

88
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:20,463
Running just makes
your blood sweeter.

89
00:06:20,547 --> 00:06:21,131
[WILHELM shouts]

90
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:22,173
[SHIROU grunts]

91
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:27,262
[chuckles]

92
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:29,723
Ha! I won't let you get away!

93
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:34,060
[REN grunts]

94
00:06:36,438 --> 00:06:37,814
[KEI]
I'll ask you once again.

95
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:39,900
Are you interested
in coming with me?

96
00:06:39,983 --> 00:06:41,735
[REN]
No way in hell!

97
00:06:43,445 --> 00:06:44,404
[REN grunts]

98
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,910
How very surprising.

99
00:06:49,993 --> 00:06:52,245
I wouldn't have guessed
you'd turn down my offer.

100
00:06:52,329 --> 00:06:54,581
You realize you're not
like everybody else.

101
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:58,001
And neither is that cocky one.
He's your friend, right?

102
00:06:58,084 --> 00:06:59,210
[REN grunts]

103
00:06:59,294 --> 00:07:01,296
[KEI]
You share a similarity.

104
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:03,548
At your core, both of
you are oddities.

105
00:07:03,632 --> 00:07:05,592
Just as I'd expect!

106
00:07:07,344 --> 00:07:11,806
[REN] Of what? The playthings
of some deranged old mage?

107
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:16,269
Well, screw you. If anyone's
the "oddity," it's you freaks!

108
00:07:16,353 --> 00:07:17,896
[KEI gasps]

109
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:26,863
[REN grunts]

110
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:35,080
[gasps]

111
00:07:36,206 --> 00:07:37,499
[KEI]
You might not understand,

112
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:40,835
but I feel completely
useless when I look at you.

113
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:45,006
I had to work hard to get to
the level you're at right now.

114
00:07:45,090 --> 00:07:48,843
You have no idea how long it
took, or how many had to die.

115
00:07:50,345 --> 00:07:51,805
[REN gasps]

116
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:54,432
And you proclaim with pride
that you don't like to fight.

117
00:07:54,516 --> 00:07:56,518
Those you treasure
stay by your side.

118
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:59,646
A happy child who
loves and is loved.

119
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:01,982
Denouncing the horrors
that I represent.

120
00:08:02,065 --> 00:08:05,527
I'm sure it makes
you feel like a hero.

121
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:08,571
I envy you, so you must pay.

122
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:12,075
[REN gasps, shouts]

123
00:08:16,246 --> 00:08:17,622
[KEI]
Formation!

124
00:08:20,792 --> 00:08:22,669
[REN grunts]

125
00:08:22,752 --> 00:08:27,716
[REN, KEI grunting]

126
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:43,106
[gasps]

127
00:08:50,697 --> 00:08:53,199
[screams]

128
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:58,621
[KEI grunts]

129
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:05,920
What's wrong?

130
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:08,381
You don't really believe you
can just run away, do you?

131
00:09:08,465 --> 00:09:10,550
[gasps]

132
00:09:15,472 --> 00:09:20,727
[KEI, REN grunting]

133
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:23,855
[gasps]

134
00:09:23,938 --> 00:09:28,902
[REN grunts]

135
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:38,995
[VALERIA]
Oh Leonhart. Still so naïve.

136
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:42,665
You should know better than to
underestimate a desperate human.

137
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:46,044
This could have been dealt
with far more cleanly.

138
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:49,839
No matter. This is where we are.

139
00:09:49,923 --> 00:09:52,467
What the hell? It's impossible.

140
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:55,428
He's been a part
of this thing too?

141
00:09:55,512 --> 00:09:58,515
Allow me to introduce
myself once again.

142
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,642
I am the Priest of the Grail.

143
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:02,894
Third seat of the
Longinus Dreizehn Orden

144
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:04,312
black round table.

145
00:10:04,395 --> 00:10:08,316
Valeria Trifa,
A. K. A. Christof Lohengrin.

146
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:11,486
A man who was cursed to
become both holy und evil

147
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:14,364
by a certain person who
answers to countless names,

148
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:16,783
but you may call
him your father.

149
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:18,243
[gasps]

150
00:10:22,205 --> 00:10:24,415
[ERI] Yeah, they're definitely
gonna go at it.

151
00:10:24,499 --> 00:10:28,086
Just hang in there till then.
He's coming up on your six.

152
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:29,504
[SHIROU]
Got ya!

153
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,813
[WILHELM shouts]

154
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:51,609
[WILHELM shouts]

155
00:10:53,570 --> 00:10:54,737
[WILHELM grunts]

156
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:59,993
Screw this déjà vu.
I'm so sick of it.

157
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:02,704
It doesn't even do me
a damn bit of good.

158
00:11:02,787 --> 00:11:04,914
Aren't you an
interesting fellow?

159
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:08,209
Surely it can't just be blind
luck that's keeping you alive.

160
00:11:08,293 --> 00:11:09,669
[SHIROU chuckles]

161
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:12,380
Yeah, well. If you ask me,
it's just because you suck!

162
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:13,715
[WILHELM grunts]

163
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:15,258
[SHIROU laughs]

164
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:18,219
There's no way you're gonna
be able to kill me right now!

165
00:11:18,303 --> 00:11:21,681
At least not without trying
a hell of a lot harder!

166
00:11:24,976 --> 00:11:26,769
[WILHELM]
You little worm!

167
00:11:26,853 --> 00:11:28,229
Okay. Now!

168
00:11:28,313 --> 00:11:29,564
[SHIROU scoffs]

169
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,034
[WILHELM shouts]

170
00:11:57,508 --> 00:12:01,054
Aw yeah! Your ass is glass, man!

171
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:09,437
[sighs]

172
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:20,865
[WILHELM grunts]

173
00:12:25,912 --> 00:12:28,081
[WILHELM]
That's it.

174
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:31,501
The time has come.
It's the day of wrath.

175
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:33,711
[WILHELM laughs]

176
00:12:33,795 --> 00:12:37,715
Leonhart will probably die
from fear. Stupid girl.

177
00:12:41,094 --> 00:12:44,889
[VALERIA] Now, then. Since you
have calmed down a little bit.

178
00:12:44,973 --> 00:12:48,101
As Leonheart had mentioned,
I wish to speak with you.

179
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:49,519
[gasps]

180
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,271
[VALERIA] It's about a subject
that is near and dear

181
00:12:51,354 --> 00:12:52,814
to both of us.

182
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:55,775
I've brought it up to
you before, but alas,

183
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:58,152
I did not get an answer.

184
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:03,241
Tell me, boy. Are you
in love with Theresia?

185
00:13:03,324 --> 00:13:05,076
[REN gasps]

186
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:08,413
[VALERIA] The curiosity
has been gnawing at me.

187
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,249
If given a
compelling reason,

188
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:14,752
could you end her life
with your own hands?

189
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:20,633
That may be the only way
for you to defeat us.

190
00:13:20,717 --> 00:13:22,343
[REN]
That's enough!

191
00:13:22,427 --> 00:13:26,597
I don't know what you're saying,
but I know she's not one of you!

192
00:13:26,681 --> 00:13:28,683
Not a chance!

193
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:31,894
And don't treat her like some
kind of bargaining chip!

194
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:34,022
Oh no?

195
00:13:34,105 --> 00:13:36,649
Then what are the rules
of engagement, pray tell?

196
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:40,069
All I'm gonna say is,
I won't let her die.

197
00:13:40,153 --> 00:13:41,738
And I wont kill her!

198
00:13:41,821 --> 00:13:46,868
Is that clear enough? I'll beat
you and end this for good!

199
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:51,956
[laughs]

200
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:55,710
I applaud your vigor, Fujii.
But it's completely foolish.

201
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:58,546
Do you honestly believe
that you could win?

202
00:13:58,629 --> 00:14:01,716
We're on a level far beyond
your comprehension.

203
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:06,137
Your goal is futile.
Absurd. Laughable!

204
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:09,223
You will put your faith in love
and thus secure victory.

205
00:14:09,307 --> 00:14:11,392
Do you honestly believe that?

206
00:14:11,476 --> 00:14:16,689
Very well. Do you hear the words
from one so pure of heart?

207
00:14:16,773 --> 00:14:18,649
Heydrich my lord?

208
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:20,526
[REN grunts]

209
00:14:24,322 --> 00:14:27,283
[REN grunts]

210
00:14:34,457 --> 00:14:39,379
[REINHARD] Not bad. I admire
that you refuse to surrender.

211
00:14:39,462 --> 00:14:43,174
Your soul is worthy
of being an adversary.

212
00:14:52,308 --> 00:14:56,646
Behold, child. I am known
as Reinhard Heydrich.

213
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:58,314
Or Mephistopheles.

214
00:14:58,398 --> 00:15:00,942
That's the title your
ancestor bestowed upon me.

215
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:05,154
A man who is very much like
the devil, one might say.

216
00:15:14,122 --> 00:15:16,457
[REN]

217
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:27,635
[MARIE] Ren. I'm so confused.
Who is that man of gold light?

218
00:15:27,718 --> 00:15:30,304
Something about him
makes me feel‐‐

219
00:15:30,388 --> 00:15:33,558
No, I don't even know how
to describe this sensation.

220
00:15:37,103 --> 00:15:39,522
You feel fear.

221
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:43,234
[MARIE]
This is fear? I don't like it.

222
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:46,237
And his power is so great.

223
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:49,157
[REN] You're right.
I have to stop him.

224
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:53,369
I must! I'll defeat
him right here!

225
00:15:57,415 --> 00:16:02,336
[REN grunts]

226
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:11,721
[REN grunting continues]

227
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:16,017
Ah. So be it. Come on, then.

228
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:21,063
[REN grunts]

229
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:43,294
[screams]

230
00:16:55,598 --> 00:16:58,559
[KEI gasps]
Sir.

231
00:16:58,643 --> 00:17:01,812
[VALERIA]
Take a good look, Leonhart.

232
00:17:01,896 --> 00:17:04,190
That is our Lord Heydrich.

233
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:05,358
[KEI gasps]

234
00:17:06,776 --> 00:17:10,279
[VALERIA] Master of our order,
and without a doubt,

235
00:17:10,363 --> 00:17:13,115
a true monster.

236
00:17:13,199 --> 00:17:15,243
His soul's incredible.

237
00:17:15,326 --> 00:17:17,912
He's managed to
absorb all that power?

238
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:20,748
Ja. He is the commander
of a spirit army

239
00:17:20,831 --> 00:17:23,501
that numbers in the millions.

240
00:17:23,584 --> 00:17:27,421
His soldiers are all warriors
who fell during the Great War.

241
00:17:27,505 --> 00:17:31,050
The Einherjar of Valhalla.

242
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:35,137
And thus far, only two
swastikas have been opened.

243
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:37,640
You should know by
now what that implies.

244
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:40,685
How much power
he's left untapped.

245
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:42,353
Then that means,

246
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:45,273
he isn't even remotely
serious about this fight.

247
00:17:45,356 --> 00:17:46,816
True.

248
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:50,528
Right now, Lord Heydrich is
but a shadow of his full glory.

249
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:54,407
No one knows what he'll be
when that comes to pass,

250
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:58,703
and I am afraid to find out.
I know only one thing.

251
00:17:58,786 --> 00:18:02,290
His is an evil that was
born in the wrong world.

252
00:18:02,373 --> 00:18:04,625
His mere presence
destroys everything

253
00:18:04,709 --> 00:18:07,044
that comes across his path.

254
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:14,510
What's the matter, boy?

255
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:18,848
Don't tell me that was the
sum of what you're made of.

256
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:22,685
Dance beautifully for me,
bastard son of Karl.

257
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:25,563
That was the promise
from the start.

258
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,953
Move it!

259
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:46,000
[REN growls]

260
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:43,140
[screams]

261
00:19:56,195 --> 00:20:02,493
Ready? On my mark.
Take aim... Feuer.

262
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:12,169
[REN shouts]

263
00:20:14,964 --> 00:20:18,134
[REN screams]

264
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:29,645
[REN]

265
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:34,191
You will never defeat me
as long as you're afraid.

266
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:36,444
[REN screams]

267
00:20:41,949 --> 00:20:43,200
[gasps]

268
00:20:43,284 --> 00:20:46,746
Disappointingly, you lack
the love for war.

269
00:20:46,829 --> 00:20:50,082
Thus, I shall teach you,
young one.

270
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:53,377
I love everything this
world has to offer.

271
00:20:53,461 --> 00:20:57,047
Und equally, no matter
what it might be,

272
00:20:57,131 --> 00:21:00,551
my love is the gift
of utter destruction.

273
00:21:00,634 --> 00:21:02,678
I destroy everything.

274
00:21:02,762 --> 00:21:05,556
Everything in this
grand universe.

275
00:21:08,309 --> 00:21:09,935
[REINHARD]
Until I discover something

276
00:21:10,019 --> 00:21:12,062
I have not already destroyed.

277
00:21:12,146 --> 00:21:15,691
Until the day I
overcome this déjà vu.

278
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:19,236
I do it all in anticipation
of the Dies Irae.

279
00:21:19,904 --> 00:21:22,490
[REN gasps]

280
00:21:25,868 --> 00:21:27,495
Damn.

281
00:21:27,578 --> 00:21:29,163
[MARIE gasps]

282
00:21:31,624 --> 00:21:33,083
[gasps]

283
00:21:39,757 --> 00:21:43,969
Marie! No! Marie!

284
00:21:44,887 --> 00:21:49,850
♪

